
Function: ODDP

Syntax:   (ODDP arg1)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - an integer.

Returns:

 T if arg1 is odd (not divisible by two), else NIL.

Processing:

Errors signaled:

 Non-integer argument.

Notes:

 No errors are detected in compiled code; results are unpredictable
 if an invalid argument is passed.

Examples:

 (ODDP 0)              ==> NIL
 (ODDP 7)              ==> T
 (ODDP -8)             ==> NIL
 (ODDP 10000000000000) ==> NIL
 (ODDP 99999999999999) ==> T
 (ODDP -1000000000000) ==> NIL
 (ODDP -9999999999999) ==> T

